headline: Recent SNAP Disruptions Highlight Urgent Need for Sustained Action Against Food Insecurity
summary: Health Net, one of California's most experienced Medi-Cal managed care health plans and a company of Centene Corporation (NYSE: CNC), today announced multiple investments in 2025 aimed at tackling rising food insecurity across the state. This initiative comes at a critical time as disruptions to CalFresh and other federal nutrition programs put increased strain on millions of California families struggling to access healthy meals.
